this receipe is outstanding. the brandy sauce is so good i am going to make it and give to freinds and family with their plum pudding at christmas.my husband loved it. i used concord pears and they where fantastic.

Rating: 4
This dish was delicious! I used 3 cups of all-purpose flour rather than the cake flour and skim milk instead of buttermilk for the shortcakes. For the pears, I used Bartlett pears and regular brandy. Very easy to make and a definite crowd pleaser.

Rating: 4
I prepared this for a dinner party, and every guest asked for the recipe. It was a perfect ending to an autumn evening meal. I used a pear liqueur called Perle de Brillet and it gave the sauce a very rounded soft flavor. I also used a leaf-shaped cookie cutter for the shortcakes.

